at is the mystery

00:10:43.270 --> 00:10:46.570 align:middle line:84%
of an ancient
telomere-telomere fusion.

00:10:46.570 --> 00:10:52.030 align:middle line:84%
The function, the precision, the
timing with which this fusion

00:10:52.030 --> 00:10:54.790 align:middle line:84%
happened, the fact that
it happened quickly,

00:10:54.790 --> 00:10:57.040 align:middle line:84%
the fact that it
is so precise that

00:10:57.040 --> 00:10:59.950 align:middle line:84%
certain redundant
functions were removed

00:10:59.950 --> 00:11:02.800 align:middle line:84%
and portions were
deleted, it tells us

00:11:02.800 --> 00:11:05.950 align:middle line:84%
that something more than
evolution has happened here.

00:11:05.950 --> 00:11:10.390 align:middle line:84%
Evolution, as we know it today,
cannot and does not explain

00:11:10.390 --> 00:11:11.350 align:middle line:90%
this fusion.

00:11:11.350 --> 00:11:13.600 align:middle line:84%
And this fusion is
key because it's

00:11:13.600 --> 00:11:15.160 align:middle line:90%
the fusion that makes us human.

00:11:15.160 --> 00:11:18.070 align:middle line:84%
It's the fusion
that sets us apart

00:11:18.070 --> 00:11:20.710 align:middle line:90%
from all other form of life.

00:11:20.710 --> 00:11:24.370 align:middle line:84%
It appears to be
intentional, and this

00:11:24.370 --> 00:11:29.050 align:middle line:84%
is where we begin to kind of
open the door to forbidden

00:11:29.050 --> 00:11:31.240 align:middle line:90%
territory in science.

00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:33.400 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sharing with
you the science--

00:11:33.400 --> 00:11:36.040 align:middle line:84%
this is peer reviewed science
that tells us what happened.

00:11:36.040 --> 00:11:37.720 align:middle line:90%
And we've just done that.

00:11:37.720 --> 00:11:42.670 align:middle line:84%
Now there's this gray, this
shady kind of fuzzy area--

00:11:42.670 --> 00:11:44.980 align:middle line:84%
why would something
like that happen?

00:11:44.980 --> 00:11:48.280 align:middle line:84%
There appears to be an
intent underlying this,

00:11:48.280 --> 00:11:50.810 align:middle line:84%
and scientists don't
know who or how or why.

00:11:50.810 --> 00:11:52.840 align:middle line:90%
And I don't either for certain.

00:11:52.840 --> 00:11:55.120 align:middle line:84%
I have my sense, my
suspicions, but I'd

00:11:55.120 --> 00:11:58.360 align:middle line:84%
like to explore some
possibilities with you.

00:11:58.360 --> 00:12:00.250 align:middle line:84%
Because the
conventional thinking--

00:12:00.250 --> 00:12:04.930 align:middle line:84%
when we hear about the fusion of
DNA a long time ago and the way

00:12:04.930 --> 00:12:06.310 align:middle line:90%
that that happened--

00:12:06.310 --> 00:12:08.410 align:middle line:84%
we're taught to think
in binary terms.

00:12:08.410 --> 00:12:10.190 align:middle line:84%
We say, well, it's
either evolution.

00:12:10.190 --> 00:12:12.290 align:middle line:84%
And if it's not evolution,
it's creationism.

00:12:12.290 --> 00:12:13.090 align:middle line:90%
OK?

00:12:13.090 --> 00:12:16.570 align:middle line:84%
Creationism invoking
religion, invoking God,

00:12:16.570 --> 00:12:19.960 align:middle line:84%
invoking a lot of things
that seem to be hot buttons

00:12:19.960 --> 00:12:22.810 align:middle line:84%
for a lot of people just
because of the implications.

00:12:22.810 --> 00:12:25.090 align:middle line:84%
And I think for
that reason-- that's

00:12:25.090 --> 00:12:28.120 align:middle line:84%
why it has become forbidden
territory in science.

00:12:28.120 --> 00:12:30.390 align:middle line:84%
Science simply cannot
prove these things.

00:12:30.390 --> 00:12:34.540 align:middle line:84%
But there's a third option, a
third option that has happened.

00:12:34.540 --> 00:12:38.590 align:middle line:84%
For the fusion to
occur the way it did,

00:12:38.590 --> 00:12:41.200 align:middle line:90%
a mutation had to occur.

00:12:41.200 --> 00:12:42.580 align:middle line:90%
That fusion is a mutation.

00:12:42.580 --> 00:12:48.670 align:middle line:84%
It means that two genes mutated
into the new human chromosome

00:12:48.670 --> 00:12:51.850 align:middle line:84%
number 2, or two
chromosomes mutated

00:12:51.850 --> 00:12:54.520 align:middle line:84%
into the new human
chromosome number 2.

00:12:54.520 --> 00:12:57.910 align:middle line:84%
Because that is a
mutation, the third option

00:12:57.910 --> 00:12:59.890 align:middle line:90%
is now recognizing that.

00:12:59.890 --> 00:13:03.970 align:middle line:84%
The third option is
called directed mutation.

00:13:03.970 --> 00:13:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Directed mutation-- it means
it didn't happen spontaneously

00:13:07.510 --> 00:13:09.370 align:middle line:90%
from a natural process.

00:13:09.370 --> 00:13:11.200 align:middle line:90%
Something directed the mutation.

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:15.300 align:middle line:84%
We don't know what
it was for sure.

00:13:15.300 --> 00:13:18.540 align:middle line:84%
And this is opening the doors
to new possibilities in science

00:13:18.540 --> 00:13:20.640 align:middle line:90%
and in scientific thinking.

00:13:20.640 --> 00:13:24.030 align:middle line:84%
So where and how
that happened, that's

00:13:24.030 --> 00:13:26.880 align:middle line:84%
where the study is
going right now.

00:13:26.880 --> 00:13:29.520 align:middle line:84%
And what the studies
are showing us

00:13:29.520 --> 00:13:34.320 align:middle line:84%
is telling a story that,
while it's new for science,

00:13:34.320 --> 00:13:37.170 align:middle line:84%
in our most ancient and
cherished spiritual traditions

00:13:37.170 --> 00:13:38.970 align:middle line:84%
we've heard this story
in different ways

00:13:38.970 --> 00:13:40.620 align:middle line:90%
many times before.

00:13:40.620 --> 00:13:44.450 align:middle line:84%
So when we talk about
this directed mutation,

00:13:44.450 --> 00:13:48.390 align:middle line:84%
it opens the door to one of
the most controversial facets

00:13:48.390 --> 00:13:51.360 align:middle line:84%
of evolutionary
theory and the ideas

00:13:51.360 --> 00:13:53.790 align:middle line:84%
and the beliefs that
support it and do not.

00:13:53.790 --> 00:13:56.160 align:middle line:84%
That is called
intelligent design.

00:13:56.160 --> 00:13:58.860 align:middle line:84%
Intelligent design--
precisely what it says,

00:13:58.860 --> 00:14:02.940 align:middle line:84%
that there is a design
that is in place underlying

00:14:02.940 --> 00:14:04.560 align:middle line:84%
the genetic
structure of all life

00:14:04.560 --> 00:14:07.170 align:middle line:84%
and that some form
of intelligence

00:14:07.170 --> 00:14:11.490 align:middle line:90%
has been the one to direct that.

00:14:11.490 --> 00:14:13.865 align:middle line:84%
For many people, this is where
the religious implications

00:14:13.865 --> 00:14:14.665 align:middle line:90%
come in.

00:14:14.665 --> 00:14:16.400 align:middle line:84%
For me, it doesn't
have to be that way.

00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:18.040 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't have to
be about religion.

00:14:18.040 --> 00:14:19.970 align:middle line:84%
It may, but it
doesn't have to be.

00:14:19.970 --> 00:14:23.670 align:middle line:84%
But the strongest evidence,
the strongest argument,

00:14:23.670 --> 00:14:28.620 align:middle line:84%
for what is called directed
mutation and intelligent design

00:14:28.620 --> 00:14:31.140 align:middle line:84%
comes from a principle
that I alluded to

00:14:31.140 --> 00:14:33.630 align:middle line:84%
in the previous episode,
but I didn't really

00:14:33.630 --> 00:14:36.360 align:middle line:84%
explain it very much because
I knew we would here.

00:14:36.360 --> 00:14:39.480 align:middle line:84%
It's called
irreducible complexity.

00:14:39.480 --> 00:14:41.610 align:middle line:90%
Irreducible complexity.

00:14:41.610 --> 00:14:42.850 align:middle line:90%
Here's what I mean by that.

00:14:42.850 --> 00:14:45.120 align:middle line:84%
If you are walking
in a field and you

00:14:45.120 --> 00:14:50.700 align:middle line:84%
find a watch, a watch
lying on the ground,

00:14:50.700 --> 00:14:55.500 align:middle line:84%
it is a safe assumption to
make that some intelligence

00:14:55.500 --> 00:14:57.930 align:middle line:84%
underlies the creation
of that watch.

00:14:57.930 --> 00:15:01.230 align:middle line:10%
The way the gears come
together and interlock

00:15:01.230 --> 00:15:06.390 align:middle line:10%
and the way that those gears
produce a function that

00:15:06.390 --> 00:15:10.050 align:middle line:10%
is useful and
meaningful obviously

00:15:10.050 --> 00:15:13.950 align:middle line:10%
reflects some
intent, some design.

00:15:13.950 --> 00:15:16.890 align:middle line:84%
And that's very different
than if we were just

00:15:16.890 --> 00:15:19.000 align:middle line:84%
to find a rock
laying on the ground,

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:22.350 align:middle line:84%
and we say, well, that rock may
have been put there last week.

00:15:22.350 --> 00:15:24.260 align:middle line:84%
It could have been there
for a billion years.

00:15:24.260 --> 00:15:27.690 align:middle line:84%
But it didn't necessarily take
any intention to put it there.

00:15:27.690 --> 00:15:29.880 align:middle line:84%
So I'm just using
that as an example

00:15:29.880 --> 00:15:32.160 align:middle line:90%
because scientists use--

00:15:32.160 --> 00:15:37.410 align:middle line:84%
some scientists-- are using this
idea of irreducible complexity

00:15:37.410 --> 00:15:42.120 align:middle line:84%
to validate this idea
that there is some intent

00:15:42.120 --> 00:15:44.270 align:middle line:90%
under this directed mutation.

00:15:44.270 --> 00:15:46.620 align:middle line:84%
What irreducible
complexity says to us,

00:15:46.620 --> 00:15:49.350 align:middle line:84%
it says that a
system can only work

00:15:49.350 --> 00:15:53.880 align:middle line:84%
when all the pieces are in place
to function at the same time.

00:15:53.880 --> 00:15:55.460 align:middle line:84%
So when you think
about our watch,

00:15:55.460 --> 00:15:59.580 align:middle line:84%
it wouldn't work for one
gear to show up 100 years ago

00:15:59.580 --> 00:16:02.220 align:middle line:84%
and then another gear
show up 100 years later

00:16:02.220 --> 00:16:04.212 align:middle line:84%
and then another gear
show up 100 years later.

00:16:04.212 --> 00:16:05.920 align:middle line:84%
I mean, the pieces
may not even be there,

00:16:05.920 --> 00:16:08.340 align:middle line:84%
or they may corrode over
those hundreds of years.

00:16:08.340 --> 00:16:10.380 align:middle line:84%
So you get the idea of
what I'm saying here.

00:16:10.380 --> 00:16:13.290 align:middle line:84%
All the pieces for the
watch have to be in place

00:16:13.290 --> 00:16:15.780 align:middle line:84%
and available at the
same time for that watch

00:16:15.780 --> 00:16:18.060 align:middle line:84%
to become a watch and
function as it does.

00:16:18.060 --> 00:16:22.230 align:middle line:84%
That idea, that principle,
applies to so many facets

00:16:22.230 --> 00:16:24.240 align:middle line:90%
of biological life.

00:16:24.240 --> 00:16:26.880 align:middle line:84%
It's kind of like the
idea of a mouse trap.

00:16:26.880 --> 00:16:30.780 align:middle line:84%
And this is an idea that
scientists use a lot when

00:16:30.780 --> 00:16:32.470 align:middle line:90%
they're making this argument.

00:16:32.470 --> 00:16:35.590 align:middle line:84%
If you look at a mousetrap-- and
it's a very simple mechanism.

00:16:35.590 --> 00:16:37.569 align:middle line:84%
But if any one portion
of that mousetrap

00:16:37.569 --> 00:16:39.360 align:middle line:84%
were not there in the
moment it was needed,

00:16:39.360 --> 00:16:41.070 align:middle line:84%
it wouldn't function
as a mouse trap.

00:16:41.070 --> 00:16:42.210 align:middle line:90%
You could have the base.

00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:43.920 align:middle line:84%
You could have the
cheese for the bait.

00:16:43.920 --> 00:16:45.420 align:middle line:84%
But if that spring
isn't there, it's

00:16:45.420 --> 00:16:46.620 align:middle line:90%
not going to be a mousetrap.

00:16:46.620 --> 00:16:48.840 align:middle line:84%
If you have the spring and
the cheese but no base,

00:16:48.840 --> 00:16:49.830 align:middle line:90%
there's no contraption.

00:16:49.830 --> 00:16:51.960 align:middle line:84%
There's no mechanism
for it to work.

00:16:51.960 --> 00:16:54.360 align:middle line:84%
So again, you're seeing
this idea in principle.

00:16:54.360 --> 00:16:57.860 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look at what
it means in real life.

00:16:57.860 --> 00:17:00.180 align:middle line:84%
And this is so amazing
when you really begin

00:17:00.180 --> 00:17:01.860 align:middle line:90%
to think about these things.

00:17:01.860 --> 00:17:04.260 align:middle line:90%
I mentioned the cells earlier.

00:17:04.260 --> 00:17:06.750 align:middle line:90%
Our cells are so complex.

00:17:06.750 --> 00:17:09.900 align:middle line:84%
Back in the early
1900s, cells were

00:17:09.900 --> 00:17:14.430 align:middle line:84%
thought of as little bags,
literally little sacks of fluid

00:17:14.430 --> 00:17:16.410 align:middle line:90%
and some sticky gooey stuff.

00:17:16.410 --> 00:17:21.900 align:middle line:84%
Science had no idea of literally
the hundreds of thousands

00:17:21.900 --> 00:17:24.240 align:middle line:84%
of mechanisms that
have to be working

00:17:24.240 --> 00:17:27.250 align:middle line:84%
in place in the cell
at the same time,

00:17:27.250 --> 00:17:30.120 align:middle line:84%
such as a cell has to be
able to nourish itself.

00:17:30.120 --> 00:17:33.450 align:middle line:84%
So the cell has to be
able to take in food,

00:17:33.450 --> 00:17:37.230 align:middle line:84%
process that food in the way
that is meaningful to the cell,

00:17:37.230 --> 00:17:39.090 align:middle line:84%
and then distribute
that beyond the cell

00:17:39.090 --> 00:17:40.780 align:middle line:90%
to the rest of the body.

00:17:40.780 --> 00:17:42.870 align:middle line:84%
If you're taking in
that food, then somehow

00:17:42.870 --> 00:17:44.440 align:middle line:90%
you have to eliminate that food.

00:17:44.440 --> 00:17:46.215 align:middle line:84%
So the elimination
system has to be there

00:17:46.215 --> 00:17:48.430 align:middle line:84%
or the cell won't
live very long.

00:17:48.430 --> 00:17:50.900 align:middle line:84%
So if the elimination
system were there first

00:17:50.900 --> 00:17:53.429 align:middle line:84%
and the cell were not taking
in food, that wouldn't work.

00:17:53.429 --> 00:17:55.470 align:middle line:84%
If the food was coming in
no way to eliminate it,

00:17:55.470 --> 00:17:56.400 align:middle line:90%
that wouldn't work.

00:17:56.400 --> 00:17:59.970 align:middle line:84%
If the cell could not
reproduce itself in some way

00:17:59.970 --> 00:18:02.070 align:middle line:84%
to create another
and another cell

00:18:02.070 --> 00:18:05.130 align:middle line:84%
or if the cell could not
repair and heal itself

00:18:05.130 --> 00:18:07.440 align:middle line:84%
in one way or another,
then the cell's life

00:18:07.440 --> 00:18:08.580 align:middle line:90%
wouldn't last very long.

00:18:08.580 --> 00:18:11.340 align:middle line:84%
All of these things
had to be in place

00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:13.560 align:middle line:84%
at precisely the same
time for the cell

00:18:13.560 --> 00:18:15.720 align:middle line:90%
to work the way it works.

00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:17.850 align:middle line:84%
Another place where
we see this is

00:18:17.850 --> 00:18:21.270 align:middle line:84%
with the function of human
blood, in the hemoglobins.

00:18:21.270 --> 00:18:26.730 align:middle line:84%
There are 20 proteins that have
to be in place simultaneously

00:18:26.730 --> 00:18:29.394 align:middle line:84%
for the clotting of
blood in our bodies.

00:18:29.394 --> 00:18:31.310 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to think
about what this means.

00:18:31.310 --> 00:18:33.690 align:middle line:84%
20 proteins-- they
have to be there.

00:18:33.690 --> 00:18:36.910 align:middle line:84%
If they were not there
with the first organism,

00:18:36.910 --> 00:18:39.915 align:middle line:84%
the first time that organism
received a cut or a scratch

00:18:39.915 --> 00:18:43.020 align:middle line:84%
that we take for granted
is going to heal quickly--

00:18:43.020 --> 00:18:46.644 align:middle line:84%
if those 20 proteins were
not already in place,

00:18:46.644 --> 00:18:48.060 align:middle line:84%
then the clotting
couldn't happen.

00:18:48.060 --> 00:18:50.430 align:middle line:84%
And that organism would
bleed and bleed and bleed

00:18:50.430 --> 00:18:54.750 align:middle line:84%
until it bled out,
until it died.

00:18:54.750 --> 00:18:56.820 align:middle line:84%
If even one of those
proteins is missing,

00:18:56.820 --> 00:18:59.064 align:middle line:84%
the clotting mechanism
doesn't work.

00:18:59.064 --> 00:19:00.480 align:middle line:84%
And another place--
I'm just going

00:19:00.480 --> 00:19:03.750 align:middle line:84%
to give you another example so
you see these aren't anomalies.

00:19:03.750 --> 00:19:06.600 align:middle line:84%
The cilia-- cilia are
the little wavy tails

00:19:06.600 --> 00:19:09.120 align:middle line:84%
that we see on the ends
of some kinds of bacteria.

00:19:09.120 --> 00:19:10.770 align:middle line:84%
We see them on
the ends of sperm,

00:19:10.770 --> 00:19:12.360 align:middle line:84%
and that makes them
really important

00:19:12.360 --> 00:19:13.800 align:middle line:84%
because the sperm
couldn't go anywhere

00:19:13.800 --> 00:19:15.216 align:middle line:84%
to create life if
they didn't have

00:19:15.216 --> 00:19:16.800 align:middle line:90%
the cilia, the little tails.

00:19:16.800 --> 00:19:18.900 align:middle line:84%
And many of the bacteria
couldn't function

00:19:18.900 --> 00:19:20.820 align:middle line:90%
the way they do without these.

00:19:20.820 --> 00:19:23.190 align:middle line:84%
And for those cilia
to work, there

00:19:23.190 --> 00:19:28.230 align:middle line:84%
is a very complex series
of over 40 mechanisms

00:19:28.230 --> 00:19:31.860 align:middle line:84%
that must be in
place for the nerves,

00:19:31.860 --> 00:19:35.330 align:middle line:84%
for the chemical reactions,
for the growth of the cells,

00:19:35.330 --> 00:19:38.886 align:middle line:84%
so that little tail can wiggle
and move in a fluid medium.

00:19:38.886 --> 00:19:40.260 align:middle line:84%
If they're not
there all at once,

00:19:40.260 --> 00:19:41.343 align:middle line:90%
they're not going to work.

00:19:41.343 --> 00:19:43.800 align:middle line:84%
They cannot evolve slowly,
gradually over a long period

00:19:43.800 --> 00:19:44.760 align:middle line:90%
of time--

00:19:44.760 --> 00:19:48.150 align:middle line:84%
just as the 20 proteins didn't,
just as what's happening

00:19:48.150 --> 00:19:49.960 align:middle line:90%
in our cells didn't.

00:19:49.960 --> 00:19:51.420 align:middle line:84%
So what I am sharing
with you now--

00:19:51.420 --> 00:19:54.510 align:middle line:90%
just so very clear about this--

00:19:54.510 --> 00:20:00.330 align:middle line:84%
irreducible complexity says that
there are some forms of life

00:20:00.330 --> 00:20:04.530 align:middle line:84%
that simply can not
evolve from simpler forms

00:20:04.530 --> 00:20:07.200 align:middle line:84%
gradually, slowly over
long periods of time.

00:20:07.200 --> 00:20:09.000 align:middle line:84%
I've just given
you three examples.

00:20:09.000 --> 00:20:11.680 align:middle line:90%
Well, DNA is another example.

00:20:11.680 --> 00:20:14.980 align:middle line:84%
DNA is a beautiful example
because it is the very basis--

00:20:14.980 --> 00:20:18.000 align:middle line:84%
it's the blueprint-- for
what's happening in our bodies.

00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:20.640 align:middle line:84%
And scientists now
are recognizing this.

