00:20:45.420 --> 00:20:47.190 align:middle line:90%
It was released in 1984.

00:20:47.190 --> 00:20:49.680 align:middle line:10%
He's a mathematician and
a member of the New York

00:20:49.680 --> 00:20:50.770 align:middle line:10%
Academy of Sciences.

00:20:50.770 --> 00:20:53.720 align:middle line:10%
So this is a very well
credentialed scientist.

00:20:53.720 --> 00:20:55.330 align:middle line:10%
And what he's saying
is this-- quote--

00:20:55.330 --> 00:21:00.090 align:middle line:10%
he says, "At the moment, when
the DNA/RNA system became

00:21:00.090 --> 00:21:03.960 align:middle line:10%
understood," he said, "the
debate between evolution

00:21:03.960 --> 00:21:06.810 align:middle line:10%
and creation should have
come to a screeching halt

00:21:06.810 --> 00:21:10.020 align:middle line:10%
because the
implications of the DNA

00:21:10.020 --> 00:21:13.980 align:middle line:10%
and the RNA are
obvious and clear."

00:21:13.980 --> 00:21:17.470 align:middle line:10%
So what he's saying is that the
moment our technology advanced

00:21:17.470 --> 00:21:21.210 align:middle line:10%
to the point where we could see
what it takes for DNA and its

00:21:21.210 --> 00:21:23.880 align:middle line:10%
complement, RNA, to
work in our bodies,

00:21:23.880 --> 00:21:28.500 align:middle line:10%
the complexities are so great
that the evolutionary theory

00:21:28.500 --> 00:21:30.800 align:middle line:10%
simply cannot explain
those complexities.

00:21:30.800 --> 00:21:33.300 align:middle line:84%
So he's saying this whole debate
should have come to an end.

00:21:33.300 --> 00:21:36.200 align:middle line:84%
It is obvious he's saying,
as a mathematician,

00:21:36.200 --> 00:21:41.850 align:middle line:84%
that there is some intent,
perhaps an intelligence.

00:21:41.850 --> 00:21:44.850 align:middle line:84%
Definitely something
is directing

00:21:44.850 --> 00:21:48.630 align:middle line:84%
this experience,
this mechanism, that

00:21:48.630 --> 00:21:50.820 align:middle line:90%
is at the core of our lives.

00:21:50.820 --> 00:21:54.510 align:middle line:84%
This hearkens back to the
very idea of our origin.

00:21:54.510 --> 00:21:55.410 align:middle line:90%
Who are we?

00:21:55.410 --> 00:21:57.090 align:middle line:90%
Where did we come from?

00:21:57.090 --> 00:22:01.260 align:middle line:84%
What is it that combined those
two chromosomes to produce

00:22:01.260 --> 00:22:03.720 align:middle line:84%
our one, chromosome
number 2, that

00:22:03.720 --> 00:22:07.410 align:middle line:84%
sets us apart from all other
life and makes us unique.

00:22:07.410 --> 00:22:10.830 align:middle line:84%
So I'd like to take this
opportunity and share with you

00:22:10.830 --> 00:22:12.820 align:middle line:90%
yet another perspective.

00:22:12.820 --> 00:22:16.200 align:middle line:84%
And for me, this is a
very personal perspective

00:22:16.200 --> 00:22:18.810 align:middle line:84%
because it involves
a research project

00:22:18.810 --> 00:22:21.810 align:middle line:90%
that I began over 30 years ago.

00:22:21.810 --> 00:22:23.900 align:middle line:90%
My background is scientist.

00:22:23.900 --> 00:22:25.830 align:middle line:84%
I was a degreed geologist
with a background

00:22:25.830 --> 00:22:28.620 align:middle line:84%
in marine ocean and life
sciences and mathematics

00:22:28.620 --> 00:22:29.970 align:middle line:90%
and physics.

00:22:29.970 --> 00:22:32.070 align:middle line:84%
All of these things worked
together for me early

00:22:32.070 --> 00:22:33.580 align:middle line:90%
in my life.

00:22:33.580 --> 00:22:36.090 align:middle line:84%
And when I looked
at them honestly and

00:22:36.090 --> 00:22:39.240 align:middle line:84%
asked myself truthfully
and factually--

00:22:39.240 --> 00:22:41.640 align:middle line:90%
what is nature telling us?

00:22:41.640 --> 00:22:45.420 align:middle line:84%
My sense at that time
early in my life was there

00:22:45.420 --> 00:22:48.900 align:middle line:84%
is something, something
more than evolution

00:22:48.900 --> 00:22:50.670 align:middle line:84%
that underlies our
existence, something

00:22:50.670 --> 00:22:53.320 align:middle line:84%
that is not being acknowledged
in the mainstream.

00:22:53.320 --> 00:22:56.130 align:middle line:84%
And while the fossils
are interesting,

00:22:56.130 --> 00:22:57.810 align:middle line:90%
I don't think they're about us.

00:22:57.810 --> 00:23:01.050 align:middle line:84%
And while the DNA is now
telling us more information,

00:23:01.050 --> 00:23:02.640 align:middle line:90%
we're still lacking a context.

00:23:02.640 --> 00:23:05.250 align:middle line:84%
And this may be one of
those places where we're not

00:23:05.250 --> 00:23:08.750 align:middle line:84%
going to find the answer
in the mystery itself,

00:23:08.750 --> 00:23:12.450 align:middle line:84%
where we'll have to find
the answer in other avenues

00:23:12.450 --> 00:23:15.825 align:middle line:84%
that help us to understand and
lead to solving this mystery.

00:23:15.825 --> 00:23:19.960 align:middle line:84%
So for me, a passion of
mine, as I mentioned earlier,

00:23:19.960 --> 00:23:25.560 align:middle line:84%
has been to look for clues in
our most ancient and cherished

00:23:25.560 --> 00:23:29.310 align:middle line:84%
traditions to see what those
clues may be saying to us

00:23:29.310 --> 00:23:31.650 align:middle line:84%
or what did our ancestors
know in their time

00:23:31.650 --> 00:23:34.766 align:middle line:84%
that we're only beginning
to discover in ours.

00:23:34.766 --> 00:23:36.390 align:middle line:84%
And I've always had
a very strong sense

00:23:36.390 --> 00:23:39.990 align:middle line:84%
that if we know where and
how to look into our past

00:23:39.990 --> 00:23:43.290 align:middle line:84%
that there are insights that
have been preserved in some

00:23:43.290 --> 00:23:46.500 align:middle line:84%
of our most ancient
texts and traditions,

00:23:46.500 --> 00:23:50.685 align:middle line:84%
insights that maybe just aren't
so well understood today.

00:23:50.685 --> 00:23:52.560 align:middle line:84%
So I'm going to share
with you very quickly--

00:23:52.560 --> 00:23:55.320 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to condense
30 years of research

00:23:55.320 --> 00:23:59.340 align:middle line:84%
into a project that
can only happen when

00:23:59.340 --> 00:24:02.610 align:middle line:84%
we cross the traditional
boundaries of science

00:24:02.610 --> 00:24:04.486 align:middle line:90%
and spirituality.

00:24:04.486 --> 00:24:06.360 align:middle line:84%
Now, I was told as a
scientist that these two

00:24:06.360 --> 00:24:08.120 align:middle line:90%
are mutually incompatible.

00:24:08.120 --> 00:24:10.020 align:middle line:90%
You must choose-- I was told--

00:24:10.020 --> 00:24:12.890 align:middle line:84%
the path of science or
the path of spirituality,

00:24:12.890 --> 00:24:15.540 align:middle line:84%
that the two were in
fact mutually exclusive.

00:24:15.540 --> 00:24:16.860 align:middle line:90%
Here's my thinking.

00:24:16.860 --> 00:24:18.570 align:middle line:84%
We're living in a
time of extremes.

00:24:18.570 --> 00:24:22.920 align:middle line:10%
We owe it to ourself to draw
upon every facet, every source

00:24:22.920 --> 00:24:26.040 align:middle line:10%
of information possible,
to give ourselves

00:24:26.040 --> 00:24:28.180 align:middle line:10%
whatever it is we
need and to call

00:24:28.180 --> 00:24:32.960 align:middle line:10%
whatever it is that exists so
that we can weave a new story--

00:24:32.960 --> 00:24:34.800 align:middle line:10%
honestly answer the
questions for ourselves

00:24:34.800 --> 00:24:37.780 align:middle line:10%
that we can thrive in
our time of extremes

00:24:37.780 --> 00:24:41.185 align:middle line:10%
so we can end the suffering and
move into a new way of living

00:24:41.185 --> 00:24:41.985 align:middle line:10%
and thinking.

00:24:41.985 --> 00:24:45.240 align:middle line:84%
And for me, I believe those
clues exist in our past

00:24:45.240 --> 00:24:47.220 align:middle line:84%
as well as in the
new discoveries

00:24:47.220 --> 00:24:49.050 align:middle line:90%
we're talking about now.

00:24:49.050 --> 00:24:51.660 align:middle line:84%
So here's what
that meant for me--

00:24:51.660 --> 00:24:53.880 align:middle line:84%
I went into one of
the oldest and most

00:24:53.880 --> 00:24:58.860 align:middle line:84%
mysterious spiritual texts that
has ever been known to exist.

00:24:58.860 --> 00:25:01.320 align:middle line:10%
And it's called
the Sefer Yetzirah.

00:25:01.320 --> 00:25:06.210 align:middle line:10%
It is a Hebrew text that is so
mystical that the rabbis say

00:25:06.210 --> 00:25:09.690 align:middle line:10%
it is not even something
that can be studied

00:25:09.690 --> 00:25:13.090 align:middle line:10%
by traditional students because
the mystery is so deep and so

00:25:13.090 --> 00:25:13.890 align:middle line:10%
great.

00:25:13.890 --> 00:25:17.400 align:middle line:84%
It's a relatively short text,
only about 1,000 lines long.

00:25:17.400 --> 00:25:20.160 align:middle line:84%
And it's only been
translated into English once.

00:25:20.160 --> 00:25:23.800 align:middle line:84%
And I took that translation,
and I read it through it very,

00:25:23.800 --> 00:25:25.970 align:middle line:90%
very carefully as a scientist.

00:25:25.970 --> 00:25:27.750 align:middle line:10%
And what I found is this--

00:25:27.750 --> 00:25:30.420 align:middle line:10%
the Sefer Yetzirah
is essentially

00:25:30.420 --> 00:25:36.420 align:middle line:10%
a step-by-step description
as if someone, an observer,

00:25:36.420 --> 00:25:40.350 align:middle line:10%
were present the day that the
universe and humankind were

00:25:40.350 --> 00:25:45.900 align:middle line:10%
created, an observer
describing the process in line

00:25:45.900 --> 00:25:49.230 align:middle line:10%
after line, the 1,000
lines, what it took

00:25:49.230 --> 00:25:52.130 align:middle line:10%
to get us where we are today.

00:25:52.130 --> 00:25:55.680 align:middle line:90%
But the text is 3,000 years old.

00:25:55.680 --> 00:25:58.380 align:middle line:10%
Whoever wrote that
text, 3,000 years old,

00:25:58.380 --> 00:26:01.020 align:middle line:10%
and it may be that whoever
wrote it received it

00:26:01.020 --> 00:26:04.140 align:middle line:10%
from a wisdom that's even
older than 3,000 years.

00:26:04.140 --> 00:26:06.330 align:middle line:84%
Whoever it is that put
that text together,

00:26:06.330 --> 00:26:07.830 align:middle line:84%
they didn't know
what we know today.

00:26:07.830 --> 00:26:10.260 align:middle line:90%
They didn't know about science.

00:26:10.260 --> 00:26:13.230 align:middle line:10%
They didn't know about the
periodic table of elements.

00:26:13.230 --> 00:26:17.970 align:middle line:10%
So I began to interpret
the text through the eyes

00:26:17.970 --> 00:26:19.560 align:middle line:10%
of a scientist.

00:26:19.560 --> 00:26:25.920 align:middle line:84%
And when the text began talking
about the elements of the earth

00:26:25.920 --> 00:26:30.550 align:middle line:84%
and of the wind and of
the sun, I asked myself

00:26:30.550 --> 00:26:32.710 align:middle line:84%
if I were writing
this text today,

00:26:32.710 --> 00:26:35.470 align:middle line:84%
are those the words
that I would use?

00:26:35.470 --> 00:26:38.590 align:middle line:90%
And my answer was, probably not.

00:26:38.590 --> 00:26:41.920 align:middle line:84%
As a scientist, when
I talk about the sun,

00:26:41.920 --> 00:26:43.660 align:middle line:84%
rather than calling
it the sun, I

00:26:43.660 --> 00:26:46.340 align:middle line:84%
would refer to the most
dominant element in the sun,

00:26:46.340 --> 00:26:51.020 align:middle line:84%
which is hydrogen. When
I talk about the air,

00:26:51.020 --> 00:26:55.010 align:middle line:84%
the wind, I would refer to the
most dominant element, which

00:26:55.010 --> 00:27:00.260 align:middle line:84%
is oxygen. And I began to
look at these overlaps.

00:27:00.260 --> 00:27:02.150 align:middle line:84%
Well, there's
another great mystery

00:27:02.150 --> 00:27:05.570 align:middle line:84%
when it comes to the
languages of our past.

00:27:05.570 --> 00:27:06.590 align:middle line:90%
Scientists know this.

00:27:06.590 --> 00:27:09.050 align:middle line:90%
Linguists know this very well.

00:27:09.050 --> 00:27:13.220 align:middle line:84%
Every language,
every single alphabet

00:27:13.220 --> 00:27:15.830 align:middle line:84%
that has ever been
known to exist,

00:27:15.830 --> 00:27:22.460 align:middle line:84%
bar none, cuneiform, Arabic,
Hebrew, Sanskrit, every Greek,

00:27:22.460 --> 00:27:25.490 align:middle line:84%
every alphabet that's
ever been created

00:27:25.490 --> 00:27:30.860 align:middle line:84%
has always had a mysterious
number linked to the letter

00:27:30.860 --> 00:27:32.420 align:middle line:90%
that it represents.

00:27:32.420 --> 00:27:34.700 align:middle line:84%
No one knows for sure where
those numbers came from.

00:27:34.700 --> 00:27:35.970 align:middle line:90%
The numbers never change.

00:27:35.970 --> 00:27:37.580 align:middle line:10%
They are a constant.

00:27:37.580 --> 00:27:41.330 align:middle line:84%
So the numbers that are
linked to the letters

00:27:41.330 --> 00:27:43.220 align:middle line:90%
of ancient alphabets--

00:27:43.220 --> 00:27:46.760 align:middle line:84%
they allow us to think of
those alphabets mathematically.

00:27:46.760 --> 00:27:49.190 align:middle line:84%
So here's what I
did as a scientist.

00:27:49.190 --> 00:27:52.850 align:middle line:84%
I compared the ancient
texts 3,000 years old

00:27:52.850 --> 00:27:54.770 align:middle line:84%
and the elements
that it describes

00:27:54.770 --> 00:28:00.100 align:middle line:84%
that make us with the elements
of the periodic table.

00:28:00.100 --> 00:28:03.260 align:middle line:84%
The ancient elements of
hydrogen, nitrogen, oxygen,

00:28:03.260 --> 00:28:06.340 align:middle line:84%
and carbon we find in the
periodic table as the letters,

00:28:06.340 --> 00:28:08.980 align:middle line:84%
and they have numbers
associated with them.

00:28:08.980 --> 00:28:12.850 align:middle line:84%
And the numbers that I linked
from those ancient alphabets,

00:28:12.850 --> 00:28:16.420 align:middle line:84%
as I looked at the atomic
mass and the atomic weight

00:28:16.420 --> 00:28:19.390 align:middle line:84%
of our elements, lo and
behold, they are the same.

00:28:19.390 --> 00:28:20.620 align:middle line:90%
They overlap.

00:28:20.620 --> 00:28:24.970 align:middle line:84%
The atomic mass of
hydrogen links precisely

00:28:24.970 --> 00:28:28.510 align:middle line:84%
with very specific letters
in ancient Hebrew, Arabic,

00:28:28.510 --> 00:28:30.130 align:middle line:90%
and Sanskrit.

00:28:30.130 --> 00:28:33.864 align:middle line:84%
The atomic mass for
oxygen links precisely

00:28:33.864 --> 00:28:35.530 align:middle line:84%
with letters in those
ancient alphabets.

00:28:35.530 --> 00:28:37.300 align:middle line:90%
So here's what I did.

00:28:37.300 --> 00:28:44.080 align:middle line:84%
I replaced the letters
in the ancient text

00:28:44.080 --> 00:28:46.250 align:middle line:84%
with the elements of
the periodic table.

00:28:46.250 --> 00:28:49.610 align:middle line:84%
And when I did that
and applied it to DNA--

00:28:49.610 --> 00:28:53.650 align:middle line:84%
because DNA is made of hydrogen,
nitrogen, oxygen, and carbon

00:28:53.650 --> 00:28:55.840 align:middle line:90%
in different combinations--

00:28:55.840 --> 00:28:58.390 align:middle line:84%
when I took the
ancient alphabets

00:28:58.390 --> 00:29:02.830 align:middle line:84%
and I replaced the elements of
the DNA with those alphabets,

00:29:02.830 --> 00:29:07.120 align:middle line:84%
the DNA began to read as you
read the letters in a sentence

00:29:07.120 --> 00:29:09.130 align:middle line:90%
in the page upon a book.

00:29:09.130 --> 00:29:13.240 align:middle line:84%
Our DNA holds a
message that can only

00:29:13.240 --> 00:29:15.640 align:middle line:84%
be read by crossing the
traditional boundaries

00:29:15.640 --> 00:29:17.740 align:middle line:90%
of science and spirituality.

00:29:17.740 --> 00:29:21.520 align:middle line:84%
And it helps us one more piece
with this clue of our origin

00:29:21.520 --> 00:29:24.220 align:middle line:84%
because the very first
sentence, the very first line

00:29:24.220 --> 00:29:27.040 align:middle line:84%
of every strand
of every human DNA

00:29:27.040 --> 00:29:29.000 align:middle line:90%
says exactly the same thing.

00:29:29.000 --> 00:29:30.730 align:middle line:90%
And here's what it says--

00:29:30.730 --> 00:29:33.580 align:middle line:84%
when we replace those letters
with the periodic table

00:29:33.580 --> 00:29:38.300 align:middle line:84%
and we begin reading the
text, the very first sentence

00:29:38.300 --> 00:29:41.560 align:middle line:84%
in every strand of DNA
literally says the words

00:29:41.560 --> 00:29:46.420 align:middle line:90%
"God Eternal Within The Body."

00:29:46.420 --> 00:29:50.065 align:middle line:90%
"God Eternal Within the Body."

00:29:50.065 --> 00:29:52.650 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't say who God
is, how that got there,

00:29:52.650 --> 00:29:53.450 align:middle line:90%
or why it's there.

00:29:53.450 --> 00:29:55.366 align:middle line:84%
I'm just sharing with
you what happens when we

00:29:55.366 --> 00:29:58.270 align:middle line:90%
marry science and spirituality.

00:29:58.270 --> 00:30:00.820 align:middle line:84%
So that gives us
one more insight.

00:30:00.820 --> 00:30:04.840 align:middle line:84%
Now that we know that we
appeared on this earth 200,000

00:30:04.840 --> 00:30:07.630 align:middle line:84%
years ago and we know
that we haven't changed

00:30:07.630 --> 00:30:10.780 align:middle line:84%
and now that we know that the
DNA that makes us who we are

00:30:10.780 --> 00:30:14.560 align:middle line:84%
appears to be more than a
random process of biology,

00:30:14.560 --> 00:30:19.370 align:middle line:84%
the question now is what does it
mean to have that kind of DNA?

00:30:19.370 --> 00:30:20.420 align:middle line:90%
What do we do with it?

00:30:20.420 --> 00:30:22.700 align:middle line:84%
How do we awaken the
extraordinary abilities

00:30:22.700 --> 00:30:25.720 align:middle line:84%
that that DNA, that fusion,
gives to us in our lives

00:30:25.720 --> 00:30:27.412 align:middle line:84%
and gives to no
other form of life?

00:30:27.412 --> 00:30:30.580 align:middle line:84%
In our next episode, that's
what we're going to explore.

00:30:30.580 --> 00:30:33.940 align:middle line:84%
I want to thank you for joining
me for this program today.

00:30:33.940 --> 00:30:35.920 align:middle line:84%
And be sure to tune
in for our next

00:30:35.920 --> 00:30:38.020 align:middle line:84%
all new episode of
"Missing Links",

00:30:38.020 --> 00:30:43.200 align:middle line:84%
the deep truth of our origin
history, destiny, and fate.

